  The quintic Ornstein-Uhlenbeck volatility model is a stochastic volatility
model where the volatility process is a polynomial function of degree five of a
single Ornstein-Uhlenbeck process with fast mean reversion and large
vol-of-vol. The model is able to achieve remarkable joint fits of the SPX-VIX
smiles with only 6 effective parameters and an input curve that allows to match
certain term structures. Even better, the model remains very simple and
tractable for pricing and calibration: the VIX squared is again polynomial in
the Ornstein-Uhlenbeck process, leading to efficient VIX derivative pricing by
a simple integration against a Gaussian density; simulation of the volatility
process is exact; and pricing SPX products can be done efficiently and
accurately by standard Monte Carlo techniques with suitable antithetic and
control variates.
